column22: field blank from ESI used to fill samples
Note the pH sensor buffer bottle fell off in transit between ESI and SAB. Assume that the pH data is unreliable.
Crew reported seeing a school of flying fish from the bridge. First time the Captain had seen them in his career. Should look for these in the Surface eDNA
Profile looked like almost no water structure reading 19 top to bottom. The engineer was also reading water as high as 21 from the boat cooling intake
Depth dropped off to 40 m when the CTD was sitting still at 34
Note I did a second download/overwrite of the afm file because I had accientlally left the Cast ID of 473A021 in the header information.
May have to stop at this station because next in the sequence is 5 miles adding one more hour to return and the captain wants to be back by 9 pm at the latest
Bottles 1-3 were on the wrong hook so they weren't triggerd. Re-armed and re-cast
There will be an extra CTD cast (Cast 41) that will not have an accompanying afm file.
Cast 42 is the cast associated with 473A023 Cast 41 (misfire) will be downloaded as 473B023

Sounder stopped working in transit. Have decided to go old school and drop a plumb line to the bottom using a weight attached to the CTD cable to get a depth, to which we will come up 5m above as a buffer since on Scatterie the depths do change.
was between 38-40 when we did the plumb line so we will lower to 35m
may have touched bottom. We went to 30 m and waited for 2 more minutes to ensure there was a firing sequence.
Bottle 5 lost a spiggot - was replaced.
Plumb line to 58 m. Decided to deploy to 51 since last time we bottomed out even with the blumb at 40 and deployment to 35
boat was drifting so some warp on the cable that might have lifted it off bottom.
Eric did cast from the top room. This means that when the CTD came out of the water, it was stationary in the air for ~3 min while Eric came down to the CTD
Have to call it a day.
